---
import ContactForm from '@components/ContactForm.astro'
import Grid from '@components/Grid.astro'
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro'
import CaseStudySectionText from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudySectionText.astro'
import CaseStudyResults from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyResults.astro'
import CaseStudyHeader from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyHeader.astro'
import CaseStudyToggleButton from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyToggleButton.astro'
import CaseStudyMetaData from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyMetaData.astro'
import CaseStudyShout from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyShout.astro'
import CaseStudyNav from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyNav.astro'
import CaseStudyImages from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyImages.astro'
import { getCaseStudyNav } from '@data/caseStudies'

import hero from '@assets/case-studies/sonata-ai/hero.webp'
import squareOne from '@assets/case-studies/sonata-ai/squareOne.svg'
import squareTwo from '@assets/case-studies/sonata-ai/squareTwo.webp'
import wideOne from '@assets/case-studies/sonata-ai/wideOne.webp'
import wideTwo from '@assets/case-studies/sonata-ai/wideTwo.webp'

const { previous, next } = getCaseStudyNav('sonata-ai')
---

<Layout
  title="Sonata AI Acoustic Risk Calculator Case Study"
  description="Custom Digital Asset Management platform design and development for Fletcher Insulation, an Australian leader in the building and construction insulation products sector. Pixel Agency built a self-service DAM for Fletcher employees and approved partners with a custom approval workflow, cutting asset support requests by 15% and replacing scattered files with a single source of truth."
>
  <article id="case-study-page">
    <CaseStudyHeader>
      <span slot="title">Sonata AI Acoustic Risk Calculator</span>
      <span slot="industry">Construction, Manufacturing</span>
      <span slot="services">AI</span>
      <span slot="duration">1 month</span>
    </CaseStudyHeader>

    <CaseStudyToggleButton />

    <!-- Single shell: all images + summary (left pane) / all case study text (right pane) -->
    <section class="pb-12 lg:pb-18">
      <Grid>
        <div id="case-study-shell" class="case-study-shell col-span-full">
          <div class="case-study-left-pane min-w-0 overflow-hidden">
            <CaseStudyImages
              heroImage={{ src: hero }}
              summary="How Pixel Agency built Fletcher Insulation a custom Digital Asset Management platform that gave employees and approved partners a single, controlled home for marketing assets, with self-service that cut asset support requests by 15%."
              squareImages={[{ src: squareOne }, { src: squareTwo }]}
              wideImages={[{ src: wideOne }, { src: wideTwo }]}
            />
          </div>

          <div class="case-study-right-pane min-w-0">
            <CaseStudyShout> Helping architects spot acoustic risk before the design is locked in. </CaseStudyShout>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The client" noTopMargin={true}>
              <p>
                Fletcher Insulation is one of Australia's leading suppliers of insulation products, serving trades,
                architects, builders, and project teams across the country. Beyond their public-facing brand, Fletcher's
                marketing operation supports a wide ecosystem of internal teams and approved trade partners who rely on
                consistent, up-to-date marketing assets to do their work. Getting the right asset to the right person,
                in the right version, is a daily operational task.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The problem">
              <p>
                Before the DAM, Fletcher's marketing assets lived in people's inboxes, on shared drives, and across
                multiple locations with no central source of truth. Marketing materials, photography, product images,
                and logos were scattered, and getting hold of the right asset usually meant emailing the marketing team.
              </p><br />
              <p>
                The result was a steady stream of support requests that ate into the team's capacity, and a real risk:
                when assets aren't centrally controlled, non-approved versions can quietly leak into circulation.
                Off-the-shelf DAM products were considered, but none cleanly supported Fletcher's specific approval
                process, and the in-house team didn't want to take on a new technology stack to maintain.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The approach">
              <p>
                Off the back of the website work we'd already done together, Fletcher brought us in to scope and build
                the DAM. We started with a discovery phase focused on the two pieces that would make or break the build:
                the integrations with Fletcher's existing systems, and the custom approval workflow they actually
                needed.
              </p><br />
              <p>
                Discovery had to surface the real shape of the approval process from the people running it day-to-day,
                not just the version that lived on paper. We mapped the asset types in scope, the user roles (internal
                staff and approved partners), and the approval steps each asset would need to pass before it was
                available for use.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The solution">
              <p>
                We designed and built a custom DAM platform on the same technology stack as Fletcher's main website, so
                the in-house team could maintain it without having to learn a new system. The platform gives Fletcher
                employees and approved partners a controlled home for marketing materials, photography, product images,
                and logos, with the custom approval workflow baked into the publishing process. Integrations with the
                existing systems mean the DAM sits inside the broader operation rather than alongside it, and the
                structure makes self-service the default path for getting hold of an asset, rather than the marketing
                team's inbox.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The results">
              <p>
                A year in, the DAM has settled into its role as the central source of truth for Fletcher's marketing
                assets:
              </p>
              <CaseStudyResults
                results={[
                  {
                    title: '~15% drop in asset support requests',
                    description: 'users now self-managing the assets they need',
                    backgroundColour: '#e8c42f'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'One source of truth',
                    description: 'for marketing materials, photography, product images, and logos',
                    backgroundColour: '#6498c9'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'Custom approval workflow',
                    description: 'ensuring only approved assets are in circulation',
                    backgroundColour: '#F37992'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'Same stack',
                    description: "as Fletcher's main website, no new system for the in-house team to learn",
                    backgroundColour: '#F37992'
                  }
                ]}
              />

              <div class="mt-6 lg:mt-12"></div>

              <CaseStudyShout>
                Sometimes the right build is the one that fits how your team already works.
              </CaseStudyShout>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudyMetaData
              client={{ name: 'Sonata', url: 'https://sonataacousticpanels.com.au/' }}
              industry={['Construction', 'Manufacturing']}
              serviceNames={['AI']}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </Grid>
    </section>

    {/* Navigation section */}
    <CaseStudyNav previousCaseStudy={previous} nextCaseStudy={next} />

    <ContactForm title="Discuss a similar challenge" displayDescription={false} />
  </article>

  <style>
    #case-study-page {
      --case-study-border: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-black) 8%, transparent);
      --case-study-placeholder: #d9d9d9;
    }

    @media (max-width: 1023px) {
      .case-study-shell {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0;
        overflow: clip;
      }

      .case-study-left-pane {
        flex: 0 0 auto;
        width: 100%;
        max-height: 5000px;
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
        transition:
          width 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          max-height 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          opacity 240ms ease,
          transform 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        will-change: width, max-height, opacity, transform;
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-left-pane {
        width: 0;
        max-height: 0;
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(-2rem);
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      .case-study-right-pane {
        flex: 0 0 auto;
        width: 0;
        max-height: 0;
        opacity: 0;
        overflow: clip;
        transform: translateX(2rem);
        transition:
          width 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          max-height 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          opacity 260ms ease,
          transform 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        will-change: width, max-height, opacity, transform;
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-right-pane {
        width: 100%;
        max-height: 5000px;
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
        pointer-events: auto;
      }
    }

    @media (min-width: 1024px) {
      .case-study-shell {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0;
        transition: gap 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-shell {
        gap: 1.25rem;
      }

      .case-study-left-pane,
      .case-study-right-pane {
        flex: 0 0 auto;
        transition:
          width 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          max-height 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          opacity 260ms ease,
          transform 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        will-change: width, max-height, opacity, transform;
      }

      .case-study-left-pane {
        width: 100%;
        max-height: 5000px;
      }

      .case-study-right-pane {
        width: 0;
        max-height: 0;
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(2rem);
        overflow: clip;
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-left-pane {
        width: calc(50% - 0.625rem);
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-right-pane {
        width: calc(50% - 0.625rem);
        max-height: 5000px;
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
        pointer-events: auto;
      }
    }

    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      .case-study-shell,
      .case-study-left-pane,
      .case-study-right-pane {
        transition: none;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    function initCaseStudyPage() {
      const page = document.getElementById('case-study-page')
      const toggle = document.getElementById('case-study-toggle')
      if (!(page instanceof HTMLElement) || !(toggle instanceof HTMLButtonElement)) return
      const pageElement = page
      const toggleButton = toggle

      const mobileMedia = window.matchMedia('(max-width: 1023px)')

      function setToggleTextColor() {
        const accent = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--accent-bgc').trim()
        const match = accent.match(/(\d+)\s*,\s*(\d+)\s*,\s*(\d+)/)
        if (!match) return

        let red = parseInt(match[1], 10) / 255
        let green = parseInt(match[2], 10) / 255
        let blue = parseInt(match[3], 10) / 255

        red = red <= 0.03928 ? red / 12.92 : Math.pow((red + 0.055) / 1.055, 2.4)
        green = green <= 0.03928 ? green / 12.92 : Math.pow((green + 0.055) / 1.055, 2.4)
        blue = blue <= 0.03928 ? blue / 12.92 : Math.pow((blue + 0.055) / 1.055, 2.4)

        const luminance = 0.2126 * red + 0.7152 * green + 0.0722 * blue
        document.documentElement.style.setProperty('--case-study-toggle-text', luminance > 0.4 ? '#000' : '#fff')
      }

      function getDefaultState() {
        return 'closed'
      }

      if (!pageElement.dataset.panelState) {
        pageElement.dataset.panelState = getDefaultState()
      }

      function syncA11y() {
        const isOpen = pageElement.dataset.panelState === 'open'
        toggleButton.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(isOpen))
      }

      setToggleTextColor()
      syncA11y()

      toggleButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
        pageElement.dataset.panelState = pageElement.dataset.panelState === 'open' ? 'closed' : 'open'
        syncA11y()
      })
    }

    initCaseStudyPage()
    document.addEventListener('astro:after-swap', initCaseStudyPage)
  </script>
</Layout>
